#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:1
msgid "Changing footer icons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:7
msgid ""
"Furo allows customising the icons that are presented in the page footer. "
"These icons can be used to link to relevant resources for your project and "
"documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:9
msgid "Unstable, seeking feedback"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:12
msgid ""
"This feature is treated as \"unstable\" under Furo's {doc}`../stability`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:14
msgid ""
"It currently needs input from documentation authors, about how useful and "
"usable this is and how \"ergonomic\" it is."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:17
msgid "Default icons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:19
msgid ""
"Furo includes two default icons, when the documentation is built on Read the "
"Docs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:21
msgid "A link to the Read the Docs project page, for the documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:22
msgid ""
"A link to the GitHub repository, if configured as a GitHub project on RTD."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:24
msgid ""
"If the documentation is not built on Read the Docs, there are no icons "
"included by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:26
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:28
msgid ""
"To add custom footer icons, you need to provide the `footer_icons` "
"configuration value to Furo. If this configuration value is non-empty, the "
"default footer icons are disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:30
msgid ""
"The value for this configuration value is a list of dictionaries. Each "
"dictionary needs to have the following structure:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:32
msgid ""
"`name`: Describes what the destination location is. This is primarily for "
"screen readers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:33
msgid "`url`: Where clicking on the icon will take users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:34
msgid "`html`: The exact raw HTML that is included as the \"icon\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:35
msgid "`class`: This is included as-is in the class attribute of the `a` tag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:37
msgid "Using embedded SVGs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:39
msgid ""
"This is what Furo does to include a GitHub icon in the footer of the site "
"you're currently reading:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:41
msgid ""
"html_theme_options = {\n"
"    \"footer_icons\": [\n"
"        {\n"
"            \"name\": \"GitHub\",\n"
"            \"url\": \"https://github.com/pradyunsg/furo\",\n"
"            \"html\": \"\"\"\n"
"                <svg stroke=\"currentColor\" fill=\"currentColor\" stroke-"
"width=\"0\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\">\n"
"                    <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 "
"3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 "
"0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 "
"1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 "
"2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 "
"0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 "
"1.32-.27 2-.27.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 "
"1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 "
