"                </svg>\n"
"            \"\"\",\n"
"            \"class\": \"\",\n"
"        },\n"
"    ],\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:58
msgid ""
"Since `html` is expected to be static HTML, you can not use relative paths "
"to images included in the Sphinx documentation set, at least not without "
"resorting to ugly hacks.[^1] Instead, it is recommended to either embed the "
"image directly (eg: in an `svg` tag), or to link to images \"outside\" of "
"the documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:60
msgid ""
"It is generally preferable to use SVG images, that respect `currentColor`. A "
"decently large set of common SVG-based icons can be found on: <https://react-"
"icons.github.io/react-icons/>[^2]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:62
msgid "Using icon packs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:64
msgid ""
"You can use icon packs that provide icons, with the footer. Usually, icons "
"pack have a non-negligible impact on first page load times and need more "
"data needing to be downloaded. That said, you also get more convenient "
"access to a well designed set of icons. :)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:66
msgid "Font Awesome"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:69
msgid ""
"With the release of Font Awesome 6, Fonticons Inc has revamped the "
"documentation to consistently upsell their [Kits](https://fontawesome.com/v6/"
"docs/web/setup/use-kit). These kits can help reduce load times on pages but "
"have limited number of page views, so we'll use Font Awesome via a CDN in "
"this example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:72
msgid ""
"If you wish to use Font Awesome icons in the footer, it's a two step process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:74
msgid "Using `html_css_files`, add the CSS file(s) for Font Awesome."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:76
msgid ""
"html_css_files = [\n"
"    \"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/css/"
"fontawesome.min.css\",\n"
"    \"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/css/solid."
"min.css\",\n"
"    \"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/css/brands."
"min.css\",\n"
"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:84
msgid ""
"Use `class` to use the relevant Font Awesome icons in `footer_icons`. You "
"can search the [free Font Awesome icons](https://fontawesome.com/v6/search?"
"s=solid%2Cbrands), and clicking on a specific icon shows the class you need "
"to use. The configuration would look as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:86
msgid ""
"html_theme_options = {\n"
"    \"footer_icons\": [\n"
"        {\n"
"            \"name\": \"GitHub\",\n"
"            \"url\": \"https://github.com/pradyunsg/furo\",\n"
"            \"html\": \"\",\n"
"            \"class\": \"fa-brands fa-solid fa-github fa-2x\",\n"
"        },\n"
"    ],\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:99
msgid "Note that the `fa-2x` is necessary to get a reasonable sized icon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:101
msgid "Different icons for light mode vs dark mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:103
msgid ""
"You can specify `only-light` or `only-dark` as the value for `class` in the "
"dictionary. This mechanism exists primarily to help you use different `img` "
"tags to present the same icon in a different colour."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:105
msgid ""
"Yes, I'm aware that it can be argued that embedding raw HTML in a `conf.py` "
"file is... ugly. :)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/footer.md:107
msgid ""
"You need to use your browser's developer tools to get the SVG directly from "
"the page: inspect element + copy svg element (ctrl+c) + paste."
msgstr ""
